{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ux6FE2tzF2CVX7xyrygo5h","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap is created in the `mongodb` namespace with the `rollback.sh` key. The live cluster is untouched.\n\n**What the script does, and why it's structured in two phases:**\n\nReverting authentication on a running replica set can't be done in a single rolling restart — if some members have auth and others don't, they can't talk to each other. MongoDB's `transitionToAuth` solves this:\n\n**Phase A** — Keeps the `keyFile` but adds `transitionToAuth: true`, and reverts the three simpler settings (verbosity 1→0, profiling mode slowOp→off, slowOpThresholdMs 200→100, compressor zlib→snappy). Rolling restart (secondaries first, then graceful `rs.stepDown` + primary restart). After this, all members accept connections with *or* without credentials.\n\n**Phase B** — Patches the ConfigMap again to remove the `security` section entirely. Drops the `admin-user` account while credentials are still accepted (transitionToAuth pods still authenticate). Then does a final rolling restart. All members come up with no auth at all, matching MongoDB defaults.\n\n**Settings reverted:**\n\n| Setting | Was | Becomes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | 1 | 0 |\n| `operationProfiling.mode` | slowOp | off |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | 200 ms | 100 ms |\n| `journalCompressor` | zlib | snappy |\n| `security.authorization` / `keyFile` | enabled | removed |\n| `admin-user` | provisioned | dropped |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":255,"cache_read_input_tokens":51908,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":255},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_